The paper deals with image manipulation and forgery detection, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) categories. The use of deep learning algorithms and unsupervised domain adaptation techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper deals with security and privacy issues related to image forgery, which may also place it under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) category.
